Heat oven to 350 degrees F. In 10-inch skillet cook ground beef until no longer pink. Drain. Stir in salsa, spinach, water and taco seasoning; set aside. Spray 13x9-inch baking dish with non-stick spray. Place half of the Simply Potatoes(R) on bottom of pan. Top with half of the meat mixture, 3/4 cup sour cream and 1 1/2 cups cheese. Repeat layer ending with the cheese. Bake, covered, 45 to 50 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Uncover; top with corn chips. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.